# Optional: the host IP printed in `make pg.endpoint` / `make pg.ip` and used
# in the .pgpass line. The ports are published on ALL host interfaces
# (listen 0.0.0.0), so any host address reaches them; this just controls which
# one is reported. Default: the source IP of the primary default route.
# PG_HOST_IP=

# Optional: override the host-side ports if 5432/5433 already collide with
# something on the host. Defaults shown.
# PG_ACTIVE_PORT=5432
# PG_STAGING_PORT=5433

# Optional: pin the backends' static IPs. Defaults are .11/.12 in whatever
# subnet incusbr0 is on (read from `incus network get incusbr0 ipv4.address`).
# The proxy forwards dial these addresses, so they must stay stable; override
# only if .11/.12 clash with something else in that subnet.
# PG_BACKEND_A_IP=
# PG_BACKEND_B_IP=
